# Copy to .env or .env.local and restart Vite (npm run dev).
# Dev server is fixed to port 5173; `npm run dev` frees that port first so Google OAuth matches.
# Must match the Web client ID in Google Cloud Console AND the same value in backend:
#   spring.security.oauth2.client.registration.google.client-id
#
# Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → your OAuth 2.0 Client ID
# Application type: Web application
#
# Authorized JavaScript origins — add EVERY origin you use in the browser (exact match):
#   http://localhost:5173
#   http://127.0.0.1:5173
# Error 400 origin_mismatch means the port in your address bar is not listed — e.g. if you
# opened http://localhost:5175 you must add that exact origin, or use port 5173 (this project
# uses strictPort so dev server stays on 5173; free that port if Vite says it is in use).
# (Add production URLs when you deploy.)
#
# OAuth consent screen → if "Publishing status" is Testing:
#   add your Gmail under "Test users", or you will see "Access blocked".
#
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
